<div class="container">
  <section class="why-solar">
    <h1>Why Solar Energy?</h1>
    <br>
    <h3>Advantages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Maintainable and reusable energy.</li>
      <li>Require little maintenance.</li>
      <li>Reduces energy cost.</li>
      <li>Require little maintenance.</li>
      <li>Silent when creating energy.</li>
      <li>Creates free energy (after recuperating initial investment.</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Panel can only produce maximum energy when pointed directly to the sun.</li>
      <li>On cloudy days, the power created is reduced.</li>
      <li>Solar power canâ€™t be created at night.</li>
      <li>There is an initial cost, but there is an eventual return on your investment.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <br>
  <section class="how-it-works">
    <h1>How It Works...</h1>
    <br>
    <ul class="col-xs-12 how-it-works-list">
      <li class="well">
        <i>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;</i>The sun will shine on the <%= link_to "solar panel", more_info_path(anchor: "panels"), class: "standard-link" %> creating DC (direct current) power.
      </li>
      <%= image_tag 'day.png', class: 'img-responsive center-block day-night' %>
      <li class="well">
        <i>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;</i>The DC power is then stored into a <%= link_to "battery", more_info_path(anchor: "batts"), class: "standard-link" %>.
      </li>

      <li class="well">
        <i>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;</i>The DC power will then get sent to a <%= link_to "transformer", more_info_path(anchor: "transformer"), class: "standard-link" %> that will change it from DC power to AC (alternating current) power that is used to power house-hold items.
      </li>
      <li class="well">
        <i>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;</i>Power that is not used can be sold back to the <%= link_to "the grid", more_info_path(anchor: "grid"), class: "standard-link" %>.
      </li>
      <%= image_tag 'night.png', class: 'img-responsive center-block day-night' %>
      <li class="well">
        <i>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;</i>If you use more power than what the solar panels provide the electric company will continue to provide power that is not from the solar panels.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
